LICENSE — The Assyriologist Cuneiform Reader
============================================

This repository contains three kinds of material with different licenses.
Please honour each.

1. CORPUS DATA  (reader.sqlite — transliterations, metadata and translations)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
The cuneiform transliterations (ATF), fragment metadata and scholarly notes are
reused from:

  • the electronic Babylonian Library (eBL), Jiménez et al., LMU Munich
    — licensed Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0
      International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0).  https://www.ebl.lmu.de/
  • ORACC, the Open Richly Annotated Cuneiform Corpus
    — licensed Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 (CC BY-SA 3.0).
      https://oracc.org/

The English translations in the `translation` column are machine-generated drafts
produced for this project (fine-tuned Gemma / Mistral models, following Gutherz
et al. 2023). They are unvetted research leads, NOT citable scholarly readings.

Because the dataset incorporates eBL's CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 material, the COMBINED
dataset (reader.sqlite) is made available under the most restrictive of the
upstream terms:

    Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International
    (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0) — https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

That means: NON-COMMERCIAL use only; you must attribute eBL and ORACC (and, for
individual texts, cite the eBL edition, e.g. "K.5743, eBL edition
(https://www.ebl.lmu.de/library/K.5743), accessed <date>"); and any redistribution
or derivative must carry the same CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license. ORACC-derived portions
additionally retain their CC BY-SA 3.0 origin. No eBL tablet images are included
(eBL images are not openly licensed).

